WEBVTT

00:02.127 --> 00:04.671
NARRATOR: Previously on
Terminator: The Sarah Connor Chronicles:

00:04.838 --> 00:07.423
COP: Been drinking?
-So, what are you in for?

00:07.591 --> 00:09.092
I'm Jody.

00:09.259 --> 00:11.010
What did you do? Did you hurt me?

00:11.178 --> 00:12.345
JODY:
Is there a problem?

00:13.180 --> 00:15.473
No, I'm her brother. John Baum.

00:15.641 --> 00:17.266
RITA:
Anything you say is confidential.

00:17.434 --> 00:19.852
The exception is if you plan
to harm someone.

00:20.020 --> 00:21.771
I would have to report that.

00:24.149 --> 00:26.150
-Jesse.
-Hi, baby.

00:27.027 --> 00:29.112
Are you AWOL? Jesse, did you run?

00:29.279 --> 00:30.947
I need a place to rest.

00:34.410 --> 00:35.910
[DOG BARKING IN DISTANCE]

00:40.958 --> 00:42.542
[KNOCK ON DOOR]

00:49.633 --> 00:50.925
Oh!

00:58.934 --> 01:00.143
James Ellison?

01:02.146 --> 01:03.271
[GUN COCKS]

01:07.943 --> 01:09.110
[BUZZING]

01:18.078 --> 01:21.038
Why? Aren't you on the same side?

01:21.707 --> 01:23.666
Skynet does not believe in you
like I do.

01:23.876 --> 01:26.544
Believe? What do you believe?

01:30.716 --> 01:32.341
You will lead me to the Connors.

01:48.692 --> 01:50.067
Stay there.

01:59.703 --> 02:01.162
[THUMPING]

02:14.802 --> 02:16.177
[THUMPING CONTINUES]

02:23.352 --> 02:24.894
[FLOOR CREAKS]

02:26.897 --> 02:28.314
There's no one here.

02:37.616 --> 02:39.951
[CELL PHONE RINGING]

02:47.626 --> 02:49.836
[ONE BEEP THEN TWO BEEPS]

02:50.003 --> 02:51.254
[PHONE BEEPS]

02:51.421 --> 02:52.797
Where the hell are you?

02:55.217 --> 02:57.301
Where the hell am I supposed to be?

02:57.469 --> 02:59.720
-We just got robbed.
DEREK [OVER PHONE]: You were what?

02:59.888 --> 03:03.432
Diamonds, cash, credit cards, IDs.
They cleaned us out.

03:04.268 --> 03:05.434
Machine?

03:06.270 --> 03:07.645
My leather jacket's gone.

03:08.188 --> 03:10.314
-So is most of the food.
-Human.

03:12.067 --> 03:14.652
If those IDs
fall into the wrong hands....

03:16.572 --> 03:18.781
Then head downtown.

03:18.949 --> 03:21.117
I'll call you with a location
in half an hour.

03:24.621 --> 03:25.955
[PHONE BEEPS OFF]

03:26.874 --> 03:28.541
Who was that?

03:28.709 --> 03:30.418
Real life calling.

03:30.586 --> 03:32.128
You don't always have to answer.

03:32.296 --> 03:34.005
I tried ignoring it all last time around...

03:34.172 --> 03:37.675
-...and the whole freaking town blew up.
-Heh.

03:38.468 --> 03:39.760
You're a funny man.

03:39.928 --> 03:44.307
Yeah. Yeah, that's the first thing people
say who know me: "Funny Derek."

03:57.779 --> 03:58.821
[BEEP]

03:58.989 --> 04:01.991
What's wrong with the system? Why
didn't it beep or whatever you set it to?

04:05.245 --> 04:06.412
John?

04:06.914 --> 04:08.623
Riley climbed out John's window.

04:10.125 --> 04:12.793
The alarm would have been turned off
for her to do that.

04:12.961 --> 04:14.420
Thanks.

04:14.963 --> 04:16.255
You gave her the code?

04:16.423 --> 04:19.216
We were up late watching TV.
She was supposed to reset it.

04:19.384 --> 04:22.553
And somehow your master plan
went awry.

04:22.721 --> 04:24.639
-Mom--
-John, our IDs are out there.

04:24.806 --> 04:26.307
Our names. Our faces.

04:26.475 --> 04:29.477
Fake addresses, fake names.
Nothing to be traced to this house.

04:29.645 --> 04:32.897
If police find who did this,
where do you think that trail leads?

04:34.316 --> 04:37.276
If our IDs made it into the system,
linked to this address?

04:37.444 --> 04:39.445
Canada.

04:39.613 --> 04:41.155
We should move to Canada.

04:43.617 --> 04:46.577
I saw your door was open,
I thought I'd bring you guys some--

04:46.745 --> 04:48.537
Oh, my God. What happened?

04:48.705 --> 04:50.164
-I'll go call Trevor.
SARAH: No.

04:50.332 --> 04:53.417
Uh-- John's been having trouble
with kids at school.

04:53.585 --> 04:55.086
KACY: Seriously?
[CHUCKLES] Yeah.

04:55.253 --> 04:57.088
You know how stupid kids can be.

04:58.966 --> 05:02.051
I'll know soon enough.
We're on our way to see their parents.

05:02.219 --> 05:04.136
All right. If you change your mind....

05:04.304 --> 05:06.180
SARAH:
I'll call you.

05:06.348 --> 05:08.265
What am I supposed to do?

05:09.768 --> 05:11.852
I'd start with a broom.

05:13.647 --> 05:15.648
[PEOPLE CHATTERING]

05:17.818 --> 05:19.235
Here you go.

05:22.114 --> 05:24.740
Come on, Rita. I got the county
breathing down my neck.

05:24.908 --> 05:26.742
We can't have a backlog like this.

05:27.536 --> 05:28.911
I'll get it done.

05:30.539 --> 05:32.832
-Today.
-I needed it two weeks ago.

05:54.438 --> 05:58.524
It's my son. He took off this morning with
the neighbor's car and my credit cards.

05:58.692 --> 06:01.777
MAN [OVER PHONE]: We'll call you right
away if he attempts a charge, Ms. Baum.

06:01.945 --> 06:04.697
-Is this a good number to reach you?
-Yes. Thank you.

06:06.992 --> 06:09.869
If you knew what was going on,
why didn't you say something?

06:10.037 --> 06:12.121
-To you?
-To me. To him. To somebody.

06:12.289 --> 06:14.999
I've always made my position
on security very clear.

06:17.461 --> 06:19.462
No one likes a nag.

06:24.801 --> 06:26.802
[PEOPLE CHATTERING]

06:37.564 --> 06:39.857
I'm looking for this girl.

06:40.442 --> 06:42.109
You see these people, sir?

06:42.277 --> 06:44.612
These people are real.
These are the real people.

06:44.780 --> 06:46.822
And they were all here before you.

06:47.240 --> 06:48.282
I'm her uncle.

06:50.535 --> 06:52.119
And I'm Angelina Jolie.

06:52.537 --> 06:54.163
Get to the back of the line.

06:54.956 --> 06:58.417
Hey. I know that chick.

06:59.002 --> 07:01.003
[SIREN WAILING IN DISTANCE]

07:04.299 --> 07:07.176
So, what do you want her for?
She owe you money?

07:07.344 --> 07:09.470
I'm her uncle.

07:09.638 --> 07:11.806
You're not her uncle. You're a cop.

07:11.973 --> 07:13.849
I'm not a cop.

07:14.434 --> 07:16.811
-You gonna hurt her?
-Yes.

07:19.314 --> 07:21.232
What about her brother?
Hurt him too?

07:21.399 --> 07:25.111
-Her brother?
-Yeah. John Baum or whatever.

07:25.737 --> 07:26.904
John Baum?

07:27.405 --> 07:28.781
Another prize.

07:32.035 --> 07:33.369
Is that him?

07:36.039 --> 07:38.332
Yeah, heh, that's him.

07:41.002 --> 07:42.837
Let's take a ride.

07:44.422 --> 07:46.382
[POUNDING ON DOOR]

07:46.550 --> 07:48.384
[FOOTSTEPS]

07:51.012 --> 07:54.723
ELLISON: Who is it?
MAN: Los Angeles Police Department.

07:57.978 --> 08:01.230
ELLISON: Hold on. I'm just trying
to catch up on last night's game.

08:01.398 --> 08:02.523
You know who won?

08:02.941 --> 08:05.734
Steelers, Mr. Ellison.
Could you open the door, please?

08:06.153 --> 08:08.779
[UNFOLDS PAPER]

08:13.160 --> 08:14.702
Yeah.

08:17.372 --> 08:20.624
-You're James Ellison?
-Yeah.

08:20.792 --> 08:23.794
I'm placing you under arrest
for the murder of Peter Meyers.

08:23.962 --> 08:25.004
What?

08:25.172 --> 08:28.174
You have the right to remain silent,
the right to an attorney.

08:28.341 --> 08:30.634
If you cannot afford one,
one will be appointed.

08:30.802 --> 08:33.554
Do you understand these rights
as I've read them to you?

08:33.722 --> 08:36.473
I know my rights. I don't know
what you're talking about.

08:36.641 --> 08:40.311
Please put your hands
against the wall, sir. Now, Mr. Ellison.

08:51.406 --> 08:53.032
[DOORBELL BUZZES]

08:55.619 --> 08:57.119
DEREK:
Come on, Moishe. Open up.

08:57.287 --> 09:00.122
MOISHE [OVER INTERCOM]: Who are they?
-New customers.

09:01.208 --> 09:03.292
MOISHE: Everything wee do,
without exception...

09:03.460 --> 09:05.586
...can be seen many ways
in the eyes of God.

09:05.754 --> 09:08.172
Or nature.
Or whatever you wanna call it.

09:08.340 --> 09:09.798
Someone came into your home.

09:09.966 --> 09:12.301
Someone took things
that were rightfully yours.

09:12.469 --> 09:13.510
The Torah says:

09:13.678 --> 09:15.095
[SPEAKS IN HEBREW]

09:15.263 --> 09:17.181
No revenge. No retribution.

09:17.349 --> 09:19.350
On the other hand, it also says:

09:19.517 --> 09:20.559
[SPEAKS IN HEBREW]

09:20.727 --> 09:21.936
An eye for an eye.

09:22.103 --> 09:24.188
We've the story
of the brothers of Nablus--

09:24.356 --> 09:28.817
We came here looking for our diamonds.
Can you help us or not?

09:30.153 --> 09:35.032
I wish I could.
But lately, business is dry as a bone.

09:35.242 --> 09:36.659
DEREK:
I called four other fences.

09:36.826 --> 09:39.536
They said you were the busiest man
on the block this week.

09:39.704 --> 09:40.746
[CHUCKLES]

09:40.914 --> 09:42.957
Well, nothing you'd be interested in.

09:43.124 --> 09:44.500
Show us.

09:47.462 --> 09:48.504
MOISHE:
Okay.

09:51.841 --> 09:56.762
These I bought in the last two days.

09:57.555 --> 10:00.349
All from legitimate sources.

10:09.067 --> 10:10.192
This one's ours.

10:10.360 --> 10:11.860
[CHUCKLES]

10:12.028 --> 10:15.990
Young lady, even if those were
your diamonds-- And they're not.

10:16.157 --> 10:19.576
--there's no way you could tell with
the eye. We have machines for that.

10:19.828 --> 10:20.869
So are these.

10:22.539 --> 10:24.039
We don't want any trouble.

10:25.041 --> 10:27.209
Tell us where you got them,
and we're gone.

10:27.377 --> 10:30.504
You think I can put a face
to every diamond in the stack?

10:30.672 --> 10:32.923
Just a face from the last 24 hours.

10:33.925 --> 10:35.676
Moishe.

10:36.678 --> 10:38.220
Please.

10:38.847 --> 10:40.055
All right.

10:40.223 --> 10:44.518
So early in the week for trouble.
But it's not for you. It's for Jesse.

10:44.936 --> 10:46.437
His name's Ostrowski.

10:46.604 --> 10:47.938
Walter Ostrowski.

10:49.399 --> 10:50.566
Where do we find him?

10:52.235 --> 10:56.071
He works out of Toluca Lake,
or so he says. I just buy the stones.

10:56.239 --> 10:57.948
And this Ostrowski...

10:58.116 --> 11:00.576
...you're sure he's the guy
who sold you these?

11:00.744 --> 11:02.328
I shall not lie.

11:03.246 --> 11:05.539
If you're so into God,
what are you doing here?

11:05.915 --> 11:10.127
Tsk. Hashem has a plan for us all.
For me, diamonds.

11:23.641 --> 11:24.933
Who's Jesse?

11:25.101 --> 11:26.310
He came back with me.

11:26.478 --> 11:27.936
He handled the diamonds.

11:28.104 --> 11:30.105
One of them killed him.

11:34.736 --> 11:36.278
Do you want some gum?

11:36.446 --> 11:37.988
No.

11:38.156 --> 11:41.158
You sure? It's cinnamon.

11:44.079 --> 11:47.122
Would it kill you
to try and make a little conversation?

11:49.125 --> 11:52.127
No, it wouldn't kill me.

11:53.630 --> 11:54.630
Funny.

11:54.798 --> 11:57.800
You're funny
in your own sort of cop way.

11:58.760 --> 11:59.968
I'm not a cop.

12:00.678 --> 12:03.097
You're not a cop. You're not an uncle.

12:03.264 --> 12:05.641
You're just some guy
who wants to kick the crap...

12:05.809 --> 12:08.352
...out of Little Miss Bitch
and her brother.

12:08.520 --> 12:10.813
Just some guy.

12:11.606 --> 12:12.648
But why?

12:15.652 --> 12:17.277
She try to kill you too?

12:17.445 --> 12:18.987
Yes.

12:20.115 --> 12:21.490
Oh.

12:21.741 --> 12:22.825
Wow.

12:22.992 --> 12:24.827
This is gonna be fun.

12:28.164 --> 12:31.375
I can't believe they stole your food.
Fricking amateurs, man.

12:31.543 --> 12:32.709
Yeah, I know, right?

12:32.919 --> 12:36.630
What do they think they're gonna do
with two-week-old maple turkey?

12:36.798 --> 12:39.341
I bet your mom freaked out, huh?

12:40.468 --> 12:43.345
-Yeah, on me.
-On you? Why on you?

12:44.347 --> 12:46.682
The alarm code.

12:46.850 --> 12:48.350
-Did I forget?
-Yeah, you did.

12:48.518 --> 12:51.854
JODY: I didn't actually see it happen.
I wasn't here, but I'm pretty sure--

12:52.021 --> 12:54.982
Yeah, I'm positive.
This is where they busted her.

12:55.150 --> 12:58.152
I heard the cops talking about it
when they brought her in.

12:58.945 --> 13:01.321
You are so buying me
these pink-and-whites...

13:01.489 --> 13:03.824
...and that is all there is to it.

13:03.992 --> 13:06.702
-Have you seen this girl?
WOMAN: No, sorry.

13:06.870 --> 13:09.204
I'm looking for this girl.

13:09.372 --> 13:11.832
I'm so sorry, John.
I can't believe I did that.

13:12.000 --> 13:13.375
Don't worry about it.

13:13.543 --> 13:16.712
Wouldn't have stopped the break-in.
Might've stopped the picnic, but....

13:16.880 --> 13:18.088
[CHUCKLES]

13:19.757 --> 13:21.884
I know you wanna find them
and everything...

13:22.051 --> 13:24.178
...but this is getting a little shady.

13:24.345 --> 13:25.888
Does she hate me now?

13:26.055 --> 13:28.974
Don't sweat it. It's a long list.

13:29.893 --> 13:33.020
JODY: You're not gonna get what you want.
Try being warmer to people.

13:33.188 --> 13:35.564
They might be more open, you know,
to talk to you.

13:35.732 --> 13:38.192
I love this stuff.

13:45.742 --> 13:47.576
That's my bad.

14:06.054 --> 14:07.221
That's the guy.

14:07.388 --> 14:09.223
That's definitely the guy.

14:11.601 --> 14:13.101
What am I doing here, detective?

14:13.269 --> 14:16.230
You've been on my side of the table.
You know how this works.

14:16.397 --> 14:19.233
I ask a question, you answer it.

14:19.400 --> 14:20.734
Why am I being questioned?

14:20.902 --> 14:24.238
You tell me. Who's Peter Meyers?

14:24.405 --> 14:27.324
-I don't know Peter Meyers.
-You killed him.

14:27.534 --> 14:29.117
Killed him?

14:30.245 --> 14:32.996
-No.
-Yes. I got a witness.

14:33.164 --> 14:36.124
Saw the murder, recognized you
from the news a few weeks ago.

14:36.292 --> 14:37.793
Recognized me?

14:37.961 --> 14:39.753
-From the news?
-The news.

14:39.921 --> 14:42.673
Twenty of your guys dead,
you the sole survivor.

14:42.840 --> 14:45.008
By now you're drowning in guilt,
I'm guessing.

14:45.176 --> 14:48.512
-Throw yourself an anchor....
-I don't know what you're talking about.

14:48.680 --> 14:50.973
I'm talking about surviving, Mr. Ellison.

14:51.140 --> 14:55.602
I'm talking about the everyday,
walk-around pain of surviving...

14:55.770 --> 14:57.688
...when others have not.

15:01.150 --> 15:02.985
I wanna talk to my lawyer.

15:03.820 --> 15:06.989
Okay, sure.

15:07.574 --> 15:08.949
Oh.

15:09.993 --> 15:13.161
I meant to ask you:
Why did you steal his clothes?

15:14.664 --> 15:16.164
-What?
-Meyers' clothes.

15:16.332 --> 15:19.668
-You were naked when you killed him.
-I told you. It wasn't me.

15:19.836 --> 15:21.503
Smart.

15:22.088 --> 15:24.548
Your alibi isn't exactly ironclad, Jim...

15:24.716 --> 15:27.843
...unless, of course, you got
a twin brother I don't know about.

15:28.011 --> 15:30.345
You got a twin brother
I don't know about?

15:48.156 --> 15:49.823
CLERK:
Dr. Ostrowski's in with patients.

15:49.991 --> 15:52.868
-Would you like to make an appointment?
-It'll take a second.

15:53.036 --> 15:55.203
Excuse me.

15:58.875 --> 15:59.916
Walter Ostrowski?

16:01.336 --> 16:03.086
-Uh-- Yes.
-You have something...

16:03.254 --> 16:04.588
...that belongs to us.

16:04.756 --> 16:06.673
Uh.... D--

16:06.841 --> 16:07.883
Do I know you?

16:08.051 --> 16:11.345
No, but we have a friend in common.
Someone in the diamond district.

16:11.679 --> 16:12.721
[SIGHS]

16:12.889 --> 16:14.556
-Moishe?
-Mm-hm.

16:14.807 --> 16:16.099
Mm.

16:16.476 --> 16:17.726
Um....

16:17.894 --> 16:21.521
Why don't we talk in my office?

16:21.689 --> 16:25.442
It's just across the hall.

16:48.383 --> 16:50.759
[CAR APPROACHING, TIRES SQUEALING]

16:52.428 --> 16:54.596
Please, please, don't kill me.

16:54.764 --> 16:56.556
-Where's our stuff?
-What stuff?

16:56.724 --> 16:58.975
-Passports, IDs, credit cards.
-Leather jacket.

16:59.185 --> 17:02.104
-Everything you stole from our house.
-Your house? I don't--

17:02.271 --> 17:04.314
Okay, okay, okay.

17:05.108 --> 17:06.441
Tell Moishe I'll pay him.

17:06.609 --> 17:09.111
I'll give you the money today.
It's in my office.

17:09.278 --> 17:12.280
-Pay Moishe for what?
-Everything I owe him.

17:13.449 --> 17:15.117
Please.

17:15.618 --> 17:17.077
Just don't kill me.

17:18.204 --> 17:19.287
-Let him go.
-Why?

17:19.455 --> 17:22.124
He's not the guy who robbed us.

17:23.292 --> 17:25.794
And go get Moishe's money.

17:29.757 --> 17:30.799
That's why we're here?

17:30.967 --> 17:33.343
Running a collections agency
for your fence?

17:34.262 --> 17:37.013
Why we're here is because
our security system didn't work.

17:37.223 --> 17:40.100
We're here because that boy
behaves less like John Connor...

17:40.268 --> 17:42.436
...and more like John Baum every day.

17:42.603 --> 17:44.646
"That boy," my son...

17:44.814 --> 17:47.149
...has been through
more than you'll ever know.

17:47.316 --> 17:48.817
Right back at you.

17:55.158 --> 17:56.366
[DOOR SLAMS]

17:56.534 --> 17:58.034
MOISHE:
My friends....

18:01.164 --> 18:02.873
Is this what you're looking for?

18:04.000 --> 18:06.501
Something for me, something for you.
It's business.

18:06.669 --> 18:07.711
This is business.

18:07.879 --> 18:11.715
-Please, I just buy the stones.
-Who sold you our diamonds?

18:11.883 --> 18:16.178
Okay, okay. His name is Tristan Dewitt.
He lives in Reseda.

18:16.345 --> 18:18.555
-Not good enough.
-It's true, I swear.

18:18.723 --> 18:22.058
He's a friend of my cousin's.
A punk. That's all I know.

18:27.690 --> 18:29.357
You killed Liko.

18:29.609 --> 18:32.694
[LIKO GROANING]

18:32.862 --> 18:34.362
Not yet.

18:37.867 --> 18:39.117
[DOG BARKING]

18:45.875 --> 18:47.417
JODY:
Never gonna find them like this.

18:48.294 --> 18:50.921
Do you even know
how many people live in L.A. County?

18:51.798 --> 18:54.216
An employee at the grocery store
saw them there...

18:54.383 --> 18:56.218
...on more than one occasion.

18:56.385 --> 18:59.054
It's highly likely they live
within a one-mile radius.

18:59.222 --> 19:01.014
[ENGINE STARTS]

19:08.898 --> 19:12.567
-I'm looking for this girl.
-No, sorry.

19:14.237 --> 19:15.445
This is stupid.

19:15.613 --> 19:18.240
Just take me back
to the halfway house.

19:19.575 --> 19:20.784
Did you hear me?

19:20.952 --> 19:23.119
I am done hanging out
with the creepy stalker.

19:23.287 --> 19:24.621
I don't even know your name.

19:24.789 --> 19:27.290
I came because I wanted
to get back at that bitch...

19:27.458 --> 19:31.169
...and I thought you were kind of cute,
but you know what? You're not cute.

19:31.337 --> 19:34.005
You're fricking Silence of the Lambs.

19:34.215 --> 19:38.301
This is kidnapping, you know that, right?
I could have you arrested.

19:38.845 --> 19:41.263
What are you doing?
Why are we stopping?

19:45.268 --> 19:47.269
[TIRES SQUEALING]

19:49.856 --> 19:52.107
Freak!

19:52.441 --> 19:54.442
[LAUGHTER AND CHATTERING]

20:17.008 --> 20:18.967
You're blocking the sun.

20:19.135 --> 20:21.469
Had an interesting morning
with our friend Moishe.

20:21.637 --> 20:26.766
He's dropping your name in front of people
who don't need to hear your name.

20:27.476 --> 20:30.312
-Well, he's your fence.
-Well, he likes you better.

20:33.024 --> 20:34.816
I'll have a talk with him.

20:34.984 --> 20:37.277
Help me out, will you?

20:39.947 --> 20:40.989
WOMAN:
Oh!

20:41.157 --> 20:44.284
[CHATTERING AND LAUGHING]

20:48.998 --> 20:51.791
How long are you planning on
keeping this up?

20:52.168 --> 20:55.003
-What?
-You know what. All this.

20:55.171 --> 20:57.547
Well, I'm certainly gonna try...

20:57.715 --> 21:01.343
...to get through today
without you spoiling it for me.

21:02.678 --> 21:06.348
Sun sets at 5:47.
I'm not missing that sucker.

21:07.516 --> 21:09.434
[GIGGLES]

21:13.522 --> 21:16.024
I'm not missing one of those again.

21:23.324 --> 21:24.658
Mm.

21:27.036 --> 21:28.536
I'm looking for this girl.

21:29.413 --> 21:32.415
Why are you looking for her?
Has she done something?

21:32.583 --> 21:33.875
She's my niece.

21:36.879 --> 21:39.631
You know, you look really familiar.

21:40.591 --> 21:42.258
Common face?

21:43.844 --> 21:45.345
Have you seen my niece?

21:45.554 --> 21:47.222
[SIGHS]

21:48.224 --> 21:50.308
I haven't. I'm sorry.

21:50.476 --> 21:52.394
The house next door,
it's on the market.

21:52.561 --> 21:55.397
-You're listed as the contact.
-That house has been rented.

21:55.564 --> 21:57.232
Thank you for your time.

22:12.164 --> 22:13.665
Wow, you guys really know
how to party.

22:14.083 --> 22:15.375
[CHUCKLES]

22:15.584 --> 22:17.252
My mom's not much of a cook.

22:18.754 --> 22:20.755
Oh. What about Cameron?

22:21.465 --> 22:23.216
She's not really into food.

22:23.384 --> 22:24.426
[PHONE RINGING]

22:26.262 --> 22:27.345
You gonna get that?

22:27.513 --> 22:29.764
No. If they need me,
they'll call my cell.

22:29.932 --> 22:33.101
Oh, right,
because you're so important.

22:34.687 --> 22:37.022
Hello? Baum residence.

22:37.773 --> 22:39.274
Yeah, just a sec. Here's John.

22:39.442 --> 22:40.608
[WHISPERS]
It's your neighbor.

22:41.902 --> 22:43.778
Thanks.

22:43.946 --> 22:47.365
-Yeah, hey, Kacy. What's up?
-John, I don't mean to bother you...

22:47.533 --> 22:50.201
...but there was a guy here
looking for your sister.

22:50.411 --> 22:51.453
-When?
KACY: Just now.

22:51.620 --> 22:55.373
I did not get a good vibe from him.
Something was just off, you know?

22:55.541 --> 22:59.586
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

23:09.555 --> 23:10.597
[GASPS]

23:10.765 --> 23:12.724
What's the matter, John?

23:12.933 --> 23:14.684
What's wrong?

23:26.280 --> 23:28.490
-Out. We gotta get out.
-Why? Who's there?

23:28.657 --> 23:30.658
-It's okay, I'll get rid of him.
-No. Now.

23:30.826 --> 23:32.535
-I'll get rid of him!
-Riley.

23:32.703 --> 23:33.745
[KNOCKING]

23:36.749 --> 23:39.042
I'm looking for this girl.

23:39.210 --> 23:41.211
She's my niece.

23:41.378 --> 23:42.754
Sorry, I don't know her.

23:52.723 --> 23:54.224
[CLICKS]

23:55.184 --> 23:58.770
-Wish I could be more help. Good luck.
-How do you like your new house?

23:59.021 --> 24:00.730
Oh, um....

24:00.898 --> 24:02.232
It's really nice. I love it.

24:04.485 --> 24:06.486
Excuse me,
what do you think you're doing?

24:09.824 --> 24:13.201
Hello, you can't just
come into people's homes.

24:13.828 --> 24:15.954
Hello? Are you listening to me?

24:18.624 --> 24:20.917
What is wrong with you?

24:30.052 --> 24:32.095
You're not in these photographs.

24:32.263 --> 24:35.181
Maybe because
I was the one taking them.

24:35.558 --> 24:38.601
Look, if you don't leave,
I'm calling the police.

24:45.651 --> 24:47.026
Thank you for your time.

25:05.254 --> 25:06.796
We were too supportive.

25:06.964 --> 25:09.465
That was the problem in a nutshell.

25:09.633 --> 25:12.051
Your son says
he wants to be a filmmaker.

25:12.678 --> 25:15.680
You tell him, "Son, movies are great.

25:15.848 --> 25:18.933
I love going to see them,
but that's pie in the sky.

25:19.101 --> 25:20.643
You need a salaried job."

25:24.356 --> 25:26.691
Thank you for not going
to the police about this.

25:26.859 --> 25:28.318
We just want our things back.

25:28.485 --> 25:32.822
"Come live at home," I told him,
"until you can get on your feet."

25:32.990 --> 25:36.576
And every time I bring up the idea
of him getting a salaried job...

25:36.744 --> 25:41.122
...he's got this project to work on,
or that short film he's producing.

25:41.290 --> 25:45.210
He's had his troubles,
but he's a good boy.

25:45.377 --> 25:48.504
He's not a boy, Donna.
He's a 34-year-old man.

25:48.672 --> 25:52.091
He lives with us, working in
a video store, robbing people's homes.

25:52.259 --> 25:53.718
Video store?

25:53.886 --> 25:57.180
-Saturn Video, on La Brea.
-Who knows if that's true.

25:57.348 --> 25:59.557
Every other word
out of his mouth was a lie.

25:59.725 --> 26:02.560
Does your son have any friends
who might know where he is?

26:02.728 --> 26:04.145
Anyone at the video store?

26:07.149 --> 26:08.608
Dave.

26:09.610 --> 26:12.487
Dave. Another boy wonder.

26:16.784 --> 26:17.825
[TALKING IN SPANISH]

26:17.993 --> 26:19.452
[DOOR BUZZES]

26:20.329 --> 26:21.829
[DOOR CLOSES]

26:24.833 --> 26:28.670
This is a very curious turn of events,
Mr. Ellison.

26:28.837 --> 26:30.672
I'm innocent.

26:30.839 --> 26:32.298
There's an eyewitness.

26:33.342 --> 26:34.759
It wasn't me.

26:34.927 --> 26:37.011
The witness is quite sure.

26:37.846 --> 26:39.681
As I would be...

26:39.848 --> 26:43.351
...if I had seen what he's seen.

26:45.771 --> 26:48.231
Is there something
you want to tell me, James?

26:48.941 --> 26:51.150
Something only I would believe?

26:55.322 --> 26:57.073
Not here.

27:03.580 --> 27:05.581
I'll be in touch.

27:07.584 --> 27:09.335
Ms. Weaver...

27:10.462 --> 27:13.131
...thank you for believing me.

27:15.509 --> 27:18.261
What good is faith if we don't use it?

27:22.725 --> 27:24.559
[DOOR BUZZES]

27:24.810 --> 27:27.770
RILEY: Where are we going?
-Nowhere.

27:28.605 --> 27:29.689
Anywhere.

27:29.857 --> 27:34.360
That guy isn't really Cameron's uncle,
is he? Because then he'd be your uncle.

27:34.528 --> 27:35.570
He's nobody's uncle.

27:35.738 --> 27:38.406
Why is he after Cameron?
Is she a criminal or something?

27:38.574 --> 27:39.991
No.

27:40.159 --> 27:41.200
He is, all right?

27:42.119 --> 27:43.453
Well, what if he comes back?

27:43.620 --> 27:45.663
It's not how he works.

27:45.831 --> 27:47.332
-I don't understand--
-He won't.

27:47.499 --> 27:50.877
That guy is dangerous. That's all
you need to know. Really dangerous.

27:51.045 --> 27:53.629
Well, I got rid of him, didn't I?

27:53.797 --> 27:56.299
I stared him down and off he went.

27:56.467 --> 27:58.343
-You got lucky.
-Oh, ease up, squinchie.

27:58.510 --> 28:02.722
Lucky is my middle name.
Lucky Riley Dawson.

28:02.890 --> 28:04.807
In that, Lucky was your first name.

28:04.975 --> 28:07.602
Whatever. Stickler.

28:07.770 --> 28:10.897
Admit it. I was a brave, spooky ninja.

28:11.065 --> 28:12.357
It was totally badass.

28:14.485 --> 28:16.319
Say it. Just say it.

28:17.404 --> 28:19.655
It was badass.

28:23.952 --> 28:25.870
I know.

28:29.041 --> 28:33.211
Fools' errands and the fathers of Nablus.

28:33.379 --> 28:35.421
-It's been a great day.
-Brothers.

28:35.589 --> 28:37.924
-What?
-Brothers of Nablus.

28:38.092 --> 28:39.425
Genesis, Chapter 34.

28:39.593 --> 28:41.052
You've memorized the Bible?

28:41.220 --> 28:44.847
Jacob's daughter, Dinah,
is raped by Shechem, prince of Nablus.

28:45.015 --> 28:47.016
He falls in love with her.

28:47.184 --> 28:49.852
Shechem's father comes to Jacob
and strikes a bargain...

28:50.020 --> 28:52.438
...to allow his son to marry Dinah.

28:52.606 --> 28:55.358
-That's brave of him.
-Jacob says yes...

28:55.526 --> 28:59.278
...on the condition that all the men
in Shechem's town be circumcised.

28:59.446 --> 29:01.114
Everybody gets what they want.

29:01.281 --> 29:05.868
Three days later, while Shechem's men
were still in pain from the circumcision...

29:06.036 --> 29:08.871
...Dinah's brothers rode into the city
and killed them all.

29:09.581 --> 29:11.207
It's your kind of story.

29:13.210 --> 29:16.421
Yes. My kind of story.

29:17.131 --> 29:19.132
[CELL PHONE RINGS]

29:20.926 --> 29:22.593
-Hello?
MAN [OVER PHONE]: Ms. Baum?

29:22.761 --> 29:24.512
-Yeah.
-This is Dan calling back...

29:24.680 --> 29:27.390
...to let you know that somebody
just attempted a charge.

29:27.558 --> 29:28.599
Where?

29:28.767 --> 29:32.562
At a bowling alley in Van Nuys.
Alien Lanes.

29:36.316 --> 29:37.442
[COMPUTER CHIRPS]

29:55.544 --> 29:56.586
[DOOR CREAKS]

29:56.753 --> 29:58.212
[DOOR CLOSES]

29:59.590 --> 30:01.007
KAPLAN:
Sorry to keep you waiting.

30:01.175 --> 30:05.720
Just have a few more questions,
then we'll get you out of here.

30:08.682 --> 30:11.225
So you say Mr. Ellison
was completely nude...

30:11.393 --> 30:12.852
...when he killed Meyers.

30:13.020 --> 30:14.187
I already told you that.

30:14.354 --> 30:16.981
And that he killed him
with his bare hands?

30:17.232 --> 30:19.609
-Didn't use a weapon?
-He strangled him.

30:20.736 --> 30:22.320
Did Meyers fight back?

30:22.488 --> 30:25.198
A little,
but the other guy was too strong.

30:25.365 --> 30:27.074
How so?

30:27.242 --> 30:30.411
Snapped his neck like it was nothing.

30:30.621 --> 30:31.913
A toothpick.

30:32.122 --> 30:35.333
Where was Mr. Ellison
before he killed Mr. Meyers?

30:35.501 --> 30:37.251
-Out on the road.
-The road?

30:37.419 --> 30:39.587
The road, the street, asphalt.

30:39.755 --> 30:41.422
Anything unusual about the street?

30:41.632 --> 30:43.049
Who cares about the street?

30:43.217 --> 30:45.009
Are you lying about the street?

30:49.348 --> 30:50.765
[SIGHS]

30:51.391 --> 30:52.683
It was like a--

30:53.185 --> 30:54.602
It was like a crater.

30:54.770 --> 30:57.021
-A pothole?
-No.

30:58.690 --> 31:01.192
It was like a complete dent
in the road.

31:01.610 --> 31:02.777
[SIGHS]

31:02.945 --> 31:08.449
So Mr. Ellison just appeared
out of thin air?

31:10.077 --> 31:12.787
-There was a light.
-What kind of a light?

31:13.872 --> 31:16.457
Bluish-purple.

31:17.084 --> 31:19.669
It made, like, a crackling sound.
Like lightning?

31:21.630 --> 31:23.422
So Mr. Ellison...

31:23.590 --> 31:27.051
...emerged from this energy bubble?

31:29.429 --> 31:31.222
I never said anything about a bubble.

31:31.431 --> 31:33.391
But there was a bubble, correct?

31:36.770 --> 31:40.565
So to be clear, you saw Mr. Ellison...

31:41.316 --> 31:43.943
...materialize out of
this energy bubble...

31:44.111 --> 31:45.611
...completely nude...

31:45.779 --> 31:50.324
...walk to Peter Meyers, snap his neck,
steal his clothes, and then disappear?

31:52.327 --> 31:53.452
I know what I saw.

31:53.954 --> 31:55.413
Thank you for your assistance.

32:09.219 --> 32:10.595
[EXHALES]

32:15.392 --> 32:16.684
Oh!

32:16.852 --> 32:17.852
Nice.

32:18.020 --> 32:20.021
Okay, so...

32:20.188 --> 32:23.983
...it's 1863 and Abraham Lincoln
is on the train to Gettysburg.

32:24.151 --> 32:27.862
But then his train breaks down,
some small Pennsylvania town.

32:28.030 --> 32:30.114
So he's gotta stay there overnight.

32:30.282 --> 32:33.451
The only problem?
The town's overrun with zombies. Zhoo!

32:33.702 --> 32:34.702
-Ha-ha.
TRISTAN: Huh?

32:34.870 --> 32:37.663
We shoot it on location in Gettysburg,
35 millimeter.

32:37.831 --> 32:39.040
Dude, with what money?

32:40.751 --> 32:42.627
What money?

32:44.046 --> 32:46.714
Do you know how much we made
just off these right here?

32:46.882 --> 32:48.799
SARAH:
Put it down.

32:49.009 --> 32:50.885
That bag you're holding, it's mine.

32:52.679 --> 32:53.763
Not anymore it isn't.

32:53.972 --> 32:55.514
This place is closed, ladies.

32:55.682 --> 32:58.392
Unless you want to get arrested,
I suggest you get out.

32:58.644 --> 33:00.269
My jacket. Give it to me.

33:01.063 --> 33:02.521
Come and get it.

33:02.731 --> 33:04.899
-Come and give it to me.
-And the bag.

33:05.442 --> 33:06.734
Oh.

33:08.612 --> 33:09.820
[ZIPPER OPENS]

33:09.988 --> 33:11.405
There's a credit card missing.

33:13.909 --> 33:16.243
Hey. Just give it.

33:16.411 --> 33:18.829
We used it on the arcades.
We'll pay you back.

33:26.046 --> 33:27.797
Where's the other guy?

33:28.006 --> 33:29.715
What other guy?

33:30.926 --> 33:32.009
Stay here.

33:42.729 --> 33:44.647
[GROANING]

33:46.191 --> 33:47.274
[TRISTAN GRUNTS]

33:49.444 --> 33:50.611
They knew where we live.

34:20.142 --> 34:21.600
Don't. Please.

34:22.227 --> 34:24.145
You know those guys out there?

34:24.354 --> 34:26.897
Were you with them
when they robbed the house?

34:28.316 --> 34:30.067
[INHALES DEEPLY, EXHALES]

34:30.235 --> 34:33.279
You were never there. You were
never here. You never saw me.

34:34.656 --> 34:37.992
You don't know
what happened here. Understand?

34:38.160 --> 34:41.871
If you say anything to anybody
about what happened here...

34:42.622 --> 34:44.665
...I'll hunt you down.

34:44.875 --> 34:46.500
I'll kill you.

34:48.378 --> 34:50.963
You wait five minutes and you run.

34:51.131 --> 34:52.173
Understood?

34:59.514 --> 35:01.849
-Clear?
-Yeah. Clear.

35:14.988 --> 35:16.197
You're free to go.

35:16.364 --> 35:17.448
What?

35:17.616 --> 35:20.576
The witness is a nut job.
The judge kicked his statement.

35:20.786 --> 35:24.580
We'll have you out of here in an hour.
Sorry you had to go through all this.

35:25.207 --> 35:26.373
That's it?

35:29.085 --> 35:30.377
You're a smart guy, Jim.

35:30.879 --> 35:32.129
Take yes for an answer.

35:32.798 --> 35:33.881
Good luck out there.

35:49.439 --> 35:51.440
[INDISTINCT POLICE RADIO CHATTER]

36:19.761 --> 36:21.804
[CLATTERING]

36:29.563 --> 36:31.730
You said you were gonna have
a talk with him.

36:32.190 --> 36:34.942
I did. It was short.

36:35.151 --> 36:38.445
-What were you gonna say to him?
-Oh, you know me.

36:38.613 --> 36:43.200
Funny Derek.

36:47.247 --> 36:50.457
-How was the sunset?
-Never better.

37:00.719 --> 37:02.720
[INAUDIBLE DIALOGUE]

37:29.581 --> 37:32.791
You never really struck me as the type
to stalk your ex-wife.

37:35.211 --> 37:37.588
I'm sorry, I just--

37:38.924 --> 37:40.674
I had an urge to see the house.

37:41.176 --> 37:43.469
See something familiar.

37:43.803 --> 37:44.845
Weird, I know.

37:45.013 --> 37:47.264
You do realize
you don't live here anymore?

37:47.807 --> 37:49.141
Yeah.

37:54.147 --> 37:58.943
Fancy ride. No wonder we keep
losing people to civilian life.

37:59.611 --> 38:00.945
Company car.

38:01.154 --> 38:03.530
They lease it for me.

38:04.240 --> 38:07.952
I have to tell you,
you don't look so well.

38:09.245 --> 38:11.455
Yeah, I'm not.

38:14.209 --> 38:15.960
I just--

38:17.837 --> 38:20.339
I don't know, all that, I--

38:20.507 --> 38:22.341
I miss it.

38:23.468 --> 38:25.386
I miss my wife.

38:27.389 --> 38:30.516
James, this is a really weird time
to start into all that.

38:30.684 --> 38:32.810
No. No, I don't mean that.

38:33.353 --> 38:35.688
Things have changed.

38:36.564 --> 38:38.482
And I just--

38:39.025 --> 38:42.069
-I didn't--
-You're not making sense.

38:42.278 --> 38:46.073
Come on. Come inside. Paul can
make coffee. We'll talk about it.

38:48.159 --> 38:50.995
Thanks, lamb.
I didn't come over for that.

38:51.871 --> 38:53.330
Yes, you did.

38:55.750 --> 38:58.711
This was the wrong thing for me to do.

38:59.421 --> 39:01.588
I don't live here anymore.

39:02.799 --> 39:04.591
It was the right thing to do.

39:04.801 --> 39:07.344
Just five years too late.

39:09.806 --> 39:12.433
Call me the next time you wanna
see something familiar.

39:13.435 --> 39:15.602
I'll send you a picture.

39:18.314 --> 39:19.773
[CAR DOOR CLOSES]

39:22.444 --> 39:23.610
[DRILL WHIRRING]

39:23.778 --> 39:25.279
[DOOR UNLOCKS]

39:27.073 --> 39:28.866
Who was it?

39:29.534 --> 39:30.576
They won't be back.

39:33.371 --> 39:34.413
Place looks good.

39:35.790 --> 39:39.626
Yeah, well, I think we pretty much got
everything back to how it was.

39:41.546 --> 39:42.588
We?

39:42.797 --> 39:45.632
Riley helped.
So how'd you find them?

39:45.800 --> 39:49.094
-Was it Derek's fence or what?
-You can't bring people here anymore.

39:49.304 --> 39:51.472
What? She had nothing to do with this.

39:51.639 --> 39:52.723
No, you did.

39:53.933 --> 39:55.476
She just made it worse.

39:55.643 --> 39:56.977
She's a security risk.

40:03.151 --> 40:04.485
Really?

40:04.736 --> 40:06.361
She's never tried to kill me.

40:09.365 --> 40:12.618
You know that this has nothing
to do with Riley. Or the rules.

40:12.827 --> 40:14.870
Or the security of this house.

40:16.498 --> 40:20.292
You're pissed because I found someone
I actually like spending time with...

40:20.460 --> 40:21.919
...and it's not you.

40:23.338 --> 40:26.340
You think I don't want you
to have a normal life?

40:27.008 --> 40:28.175
No. I don't.

40:28.426 --> 40:31.178
Hey. We didn't choose this, John.
It chose us.

40:31.429 --> 40:35.099
And there's nothing either of us can
do about it. My job is to protect you.

40:35.266 --> 40:37.267
And you can hate me
as much as you want...

40:37.435 --> 40:40.104
...but I will keep doing that
as long as I'm here.

40:42.357 --> 40:45.317
Then why didn't you protect me
when I was killing Sarkissian?

40:48.196 --> 40:52.116
Why didn't you protect me
when I had my hands around his throat?

40:53.034 --> 40:56.411
Why didn't you protect me from that?

41:10.677 --> 41:12.386
WEAVER:
It's a moray.

41:12.554 --> 41:15.222
They're nocturnal predators.

41:15.723 --> 41:16.723
Does it have a name?

41:16.933 --> 41:18.851
No. It doesn't.

41:19.018 --> 41:21.562
Please. Sit.

41:28.194 --> 41:30.070
I read the witness report.

41:30.238 --> 41:31.446
So did l.

41:32.240 --> 41:34.408
He comes across as crazy,
doesn't he?

41:34.576 --> 41:36.160
Who wouldn't?

41:36.369 --> 41:37.911
You, if you'd tell me the truth.

41:39.747 --> 41:42.749
There was another one of you,
wasn't there? A twin?

41:43.751 --> 41:45.252
Yes.

41:45.420 --> 41:47.337
Where is it now?

41:47.589 --> 41:48.839
I don't know.

41:49.382 --> 41:50.591
Why did it come?

41:52.260 --> 41:53.844
I think I'm being tested.

41:54.888 --> 41:56.555
Like Job?

41:59.684 --> 42:00.726
You know the story?

42:00.894 --> 42:03.187
He suffered worse
than any man before him.

42:03.354 --> 42:05.189
Everything he loved was taken away.

42:07.984 --> 42:10.110
Everything but his life.

42:11.196 --> 42:13.780
But he didn't renounce God.

42:14.115 --> 42:15.240
And God spared him.

42:18.786 --> 42:22.372
So who spared you?

42:35.136 --> 42:37.221
[CRYING]

42:37.388 --> 42:39.640
Where did you get those credit cards?

42:42.060 --> 42:43.810
I don't know.

42:48.399 --> 42:49.816
Yes, you do.

42:57.909 --> 42:59.576
She said...

43:00.286 --> 43:01.578
...she would find me.

43:03.790 --> 43:06.166
She said she would kill me.

43:08.294 --> 43:10.337
I promise you...

43:11.005 --> 43:13.006
...she won't.
